All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    Album
    An Album object contains a list of songs from the librairy.
    AlbumList
    AlbumList is the class containing all albums in a list.
    Categories
    Categorie is an enum used to attribute a category to an audio book.
    Chanson
    Chanson is a song object in the librairy.
    DeserializeFromXML
    DeserializeFromXML allow the deserialization of all objects of the librairy.
    Element
    Element is the base class for Chanson and LivreAudio.
    ElementList
    ElementList is the class containing all elements in a list.
    Genres
    Genres is an enum used to attribute a type to a song.
    interfaceJmusicHub
    interfaceJmusicHub contains the prototypes of the methods for the creation of new songs, audio books, albums and playists in jMusicHub.
    IntLogger
    IntLogger contains the write() method for SingletonFileLogger and SingletonConsoleLogger.
    jMusicHub
    jMusicHub contains the main method for the program.
    Langues
    Langues is an enum used to attribute a language to an audio book.
    Levels
    Levels is an enum used to attribute a type to a message in the logs.
    LivreAudio
    LivreAudio is an audio book object in the librairy.
    Playlist
    A Playlist object contains a list of songs and audio books from the librairy.
    PlaylistList
    PlaylistList is the class containing all playlists in a list.
    SerializeToXML
    SerializeToXML allow the serialization of all objects of the librairy.
    SingletonConsoleLogger
    Singleton class to display a message to the user.
    SingletonFileLogger
    Singleton class to write a message in the logfile.
    UserList
    UserList is the parent class of ElementList, AlbumList and PlaylistList.
    WrongEnumValue
    WrongEnumValue is an exception created when the value entered by the user is not in the enum list.
